The '''United States Senate election of 1892''' was an election which, corresponding with former President [[Grover Cleveland]]'s [[United States presidential election, 1892|return to power]], had the [[Republican Party (United States)| Republican Party]] lose seven  seats in the [[United States Senate]] and lose its majority to the [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic Party]].

As this election was prior to ratification of the [[Seventeenth Amendment to the United States Constitution|seventeenth amendment]], Senators were chosen by [[State legislature (United States)|State legislatures]].

== Results ==
[[53rd United States Congress|53rd Congress]] (1893â1895) 

* Majority Party: Democratic (44)
* Minority Party: Republican (37)
* Other Parties: Populist (3); Silver (1)
* '''Total Seats: 88'''
* Vacant: 3

